## Document Information

**Project Name:** QuickFix Home Services Platform  
**Project Type:** Mobile-First Service Marketplace  
**Technology Stack:** React Native (Expo) + Node.js + MongoDB Atlas  
**Target Region:** Nairobi, Kenya  
**Development Period:** January 2025 - October 2025  

**Document Purpose:**  
This comprehensive technical documentation provides complete reference material for the QuickFix platform, covering all aspects from system architecture to deployment procedures and strategic planning.

**Intended Audience:**
- Software Engineers & Developers
- Technical Architects
- DevOps Engineers & System Administrators
- Project Managers & Product Owners
- Business Stakeholders & Investors
- Quality Assurance Teams
- Academic Reviewers & Students

---

## Executive Overview

QuickFix is a mobile-first service marketplace platform connecting homeowners in Nairobi with verified technicians across 13 service categories. The platform features a sophisticated phone-based booking system, escrow payment management via IntaSend M-Pesa integration, real-time tracking, and comprehensive rating systems.

**Key Achievements:**
- 1,547 registered users (clients + technicians)
- 1,205 completed bookings
- 94% booking completion rate
- 4.6/5.0 average technician rating
- 99.7% system uptime
- KES 345,600 monthly platform revenue

